                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " A 14.5 MeV deuteron beam was focused",
                "        onto a tritium gas target cell (2.5 bar H-3,",
                "        12 micro-meter thick Mo-foil), cooled",
                "        by liquid nitrogen."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".Deuterated scintillating target (NE213(D),",
                " 7.6cm x 5cm diam.)"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "   205 cm from the source to the target",
                "        and a mean distance of 75 cm from the",
                "        target to the detectors.",
                ".In the 30 degrees direction highly polarised",
                " neutrons (polarisation was 0.73+-0.04) of 29.6 MeV",
                " passed a heavy metal collimator and a spin",
                " rotation magnet.",
                ".Recoil energy, pulse-shape information and",
                " time-of-flight were measured simultaneously."
              ]
            }
          ],
